The woman reported the incident to local police after the officer demanded a wallet, a cellphone and bank cards after he gave her a lift. CAPE TOWN - A police constable remains in custody after he was arrested for allegedly robbing a woman at gunpoint. The woman reported the incident to local police, resulting in the 36-year-old officer's arrest last night. The police s Siphokazi Mawisa said: &quot;It is alleged the officer drew out a firearm and demanded a cellphone and a wallet after he assisted the victim with a lift from King Williams Town. He then turned to a gravel road next to Mzansi Location, where he robbed her and also demanded bank cards.&quot;(Edited by Refilwe Thobega)